Dear @ngrilli
Thank you for your reply.
Actually the creep rate I am considering is related to  the principal stresses in three directions, i.e. έ=f(σ1,σ2,σ3).
The question may not be solved by just changing the expression for "effective_trial_stress" in RadialReturnStressUpdate.
Besides, i tried to realize this creep calculation by creating a  new class "CreepTest" derived from RadialReturnCreepStressUpdateBase  as shown in the following codes，but the calculation didn't converge.
Real
CreepTest::computeResidual(const Real effective_trial_stress, const Real scalar)
{
  _stress1[_qp] = RankTwoScalarTools::maxPrincipal(_stress[_qp], _input_direction);
  _stress2[_qp] = RankTwoScalarTools::midPrincipal(_stress[_qp], _input_direction);
  _stress3[_qp] = RankTwoScalarTools::minPrincipal(_stress[_qp], _input_direction);

  _creep_rate[_qp] = function(_stress1[_qp] ,_stress2[_qp] ,_stress3[_qp] )
  return _creep_rate[_qp] - scalar/_dt;
}

Real
CreepTest::computeDerivative(const Real effective_trial_stress, const Real scalar)
{
  return 0.0 - 1/_dt;
}
